OL,3,CBenefits law 'breaches human rights'
OL,4,Cafter man is denied pension
OL,6,FA carer who looks after his two
OL,7,Fdisabled children says being denied
OL,8,Fhis state pension is a breach of his
OL,9,Fhuman rights, and he's lodged a formal
OL,10,Fcomplaint.
OL,12,F69-year-old Mark Jones is being denied
OL,13,Fa pension that he has paid into all
OL,14,Fhis life, because he already receives
OL,15,Fcarer benefits from Jersey's
OL,16,FGovernment.
OL,18,FIndividuals cannot receive the two
OL,19,Fbenefits because it would breach the
OL,20,F1975 Social Security Overlapping of
OL,21,FBenefits Order.
