OL,3,CBenefits law 'breaches human rights'
OL,4,Cafter man is denied pension
OL,6,FA Freedom of Information request from
OL,7,FFebruary 2024 found there were 17
OL,8,Fpeople in Mark's situation, and he
OL,9,Festimates that would cost the
OL,10,Fgovernment #220,000 a year - which
OL,11,Fwould also be taxed.
OL,13,FAge Concern Jersey is backing his
OL,14,Fcall, with the group's chair labelling
OL,15,Fthe current regulations inhumane.
OL,17,FBen Shenton, Chairman of Age Concern
OL,18,FJersey, says: "Guernsey changed the
OL,19,Flaw seven years ago so they showed
OL,20,Fcommon sense and compassion, where we
OL,21,Fshowed none.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G5/7
